fy_powder (beta 1) by Dr. Spud
I made this map as a throwback to my days of making CS maps. It was fun. And I had all these nice snow assets laying around doing nothing, so I figured I might as well stick them in a map. You might point that this map has a rather large file size and is more fps-taxing than other fy maps. But at this point I'm not really concerned about that anymore. I don't think I'm going to be dethroning the fy maps that get played nowadays, so what's the harm in cranking up the graphics. Plus it's a fun little arena, with a touch more interesting-ness than your average fy_iceworld or fy_snow.
Features
  • Dozens of new models and textures
  • Snow and fog that changes direction with the wind.
  • All your regular amenities like overview radar, HDR, etc.
  • 48 spawns

Simple Glass map that isn't to visually impressive, but tons of fun to play. Testing it was a bast. Consists of two houses constructed completely of pressure sensitive glass, along with the floor below. There are steel supports for the glass allowing the player to have some mobility after all the glass is broken, below that is a pit where everyone dies.... You are allowed a knife and a P228 Compact Pistol in this map, nothing else. In the middle is a concrete and bullet proof maze leading to two kill switches. Each button demolishes one of the houses in the map potentially ending the game as it kills everyone inside. It may be a little CPU intensive, but the lag subsides quite quickly on older systems. The roof collapses crushing everything below it....

A few new props and textures go a long way to bring the original fy_pool_day feeling back to the new Source engine in fy_pool_sourcness.

Map supports 16 players! from the original 14.
New weapons- Famas and Galil
Included are the materials and bot navigation files.

This map is a remake of my all time favorite map from a long time ago. It was called fy_pool_day2 and it was for counter-strike. I have not played on the original map in several years. I made this version using only my memory and a few screenshots. This is a somewhat fast paced shoot-em-up with some places to hide. There is however a bombsite at the top of the highdive. It also has an underwater passage way to both spawn areas. Just a nice little map for some clean fun. Can't you just feel that cool refreashing water hitting your face? :)
